    "en": "area occupied in the seating plane of the geometrical object defined by its effective physical contour"
  },
  "synonyms": [],
  "remark": "- The net area is defined as a plane normally not possible to be occupied by other geometrical objects |\r\n - The net area lies in the seating plane defined by the x/y- axes of the object and can be mathematically derived from the net space |\r\n - Seating plane is that plane on which the geometrical object is fixed.",
